---
import UseCase from '../../../UseCase.astro';
import UseCaseInteractive from '../../../UseCaseInteractive.astro';
import Usage from '../../../Usage.astro';
import UsageItem from '../../../UsageItem.astro';
import Markdown from '../../../Markdown.astro';
import AIBalloon from '../../AIBalloon.astro';
import AIBalloonMessage from '../../AIBalloonMessage.astro';
import AIResponseMessage from '../../AIResponseMessage.astro';
import HighlightBox from '../../HighlightBox.astro';
---

<UseCase
  title="Concise, Goal-Oriented AI Output"
  description="Keep AI responses focused on the user's question or task—concise and actionable, without unnecessary preamble, repetition, or tangents."
>
  <UseCaseInteractive clsHeight={112} label="Concise, goal-oriented output" toggle>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>
          I received an order with two products, one of which is defective. How do I get a refund?
        </AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <HighlightBox label="resolution actions" variant="success">
          <Markdown
            typography="detail"
            content={`
You can request a refund only for the defective item:

1. Go to My Orders
2. Select the order
3. Click Request Refund next to the defective product
4. Choose damaged product as the reason
5. Follow the return instructions (if requested)

Refunds are processed **within 5-7 days of confirmation.**
        `}
          />
        </HighlightBox>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
    <div class="grid gap-600 w-full max-w-9600">
      <AIBalloon>
        <AIBalloonMessage>
          I received an order with two products, one of which is defective. How do I get a refund?
        </AIBalloonMessage>
      </AIBalloon>
      <AIResponseMessage>
        <HighlightBox label="unnecessarily detailed" variant="error">
          <Markdown
            typography="detail"
            content={`
When it comes to refunds, it's important to consider several aspects related to company policies, which can vary depending on the seller, the type of product, and the general terms and conditions of sale.

In many cases, defective products can be returned within a certain period of time, often 14 or 30 days, but this depends on various factors.

Furthermore, some companies require photographic evidence of the defect, while others may proceed directly with a replacement rather than a refund.

In your specific case, having purchased two items, you may need to distinguish between the defective product and the functioning one, checking whether a partial refund is possible or whether the order should be processed as a whole.

I would therefore recommend accessing the orders section, reviewing the details, carefully reading the terms and conditions, and, if necessary, contacting customer support for additional clarification, to determine which procedure is best for your situation.
        `}
          />
        </HighlightBox>
      </AIResponseMessage>
    </div>
  </UseCaseInteractive>
  <Usage>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Lead with the answer or outcome; keep text short and tied to the user's goal.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Pad responses with long preambles, repeated phrasing, or tangents that don't support the task.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="do">
      Use lists, bullets, or short paragraphs so users can scan and act quickly.
    </UsageItem>
    <UsageItem variant="dont">
      Default to long prose when a few lines or a structured summary would suffice.
    </UsageItem>
  </Usage>
</UseCase>
